President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring November 24 through November 30, 2013 as National Family Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of families in American society, regardless of their composition, and encourages the celebration of family bonds. The President also highlights his administration's efforts to support families through initiatives such as job creation, affordable health insurance, and education. He calls on Congress to increase the minimum wage and praises the Joining Forces initiative led by First Lady Michelle Obama and Dr. Jill Biden, which connects military families with employment opportunities. The proclamation concludes by inviting all states, communities, and individuals to observe National Family Week through appropriate ceremonies and activities.